## What does a copywriter need to do?
* Write texts on a wide variety of topics, mainly in English.
* Be competent in conveying information in simple terms.
* Generate ideas.
* Just be in a good mood.
## We guarantee:
* Work from home. Work in comfortable conditions;
* An opportunity to try yourself in the new field and improve already existing skills;
* Career growth from copywriter to marketer;
* Interesting and creative tasks;
* The ability to work with foreign customers;
* Decent salary and understanding leaders.
We also offer the possibility of further training in **marketing specialties** such as **SEO**, **SMM**, and **Content Manager**. Alternatively, you can try yourself to be a **Proofreader**, **Rewriter**, **SEO-copywriter**, and **Content Manager**.
We expect your English to be above an intermediate level; you to be diligent, attentive, and ready to learn. We also expect responsibility, punctuality, creativity, and result-orientation from you.
## Copywriter Vacancy
If you think you are a suitable candidate for this job, then send us your contacts and CV as soon as possible.

## Required skills:
* knowledge and understanding of the search engine’s algorithm;
* work experience with SEO services and programs (Google Planner, Google Search Console, Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, Bright Local, Spyfu, Ahrefs);
* the basics of copywriting;
* skills of useful content creation;
* creative thinking.
## Responsibilities include:
* search engine optimization – the site should remain high in the search results;
* report on the work undertaken;
* determining the project execution deadlines;
* assignment of tasks among team members;
* motivation of employees, promotion of their professional and career growth.
## Apply for the vacancy
If you are responsible, sociable, eager to develop in the field of SEO, and speak English fluently, leave the application below, we will definitely contact you!.  
## Advantages of working in our company:
* Good, stable salary
* Career opportunities
* On-the-job training
* Young, professional, positive, and friendly team
* Convenient work schedule

## Who is an Email Marketer?
An email marketer is a specialist who provides email marketing services and creates and distributes emails to users’ addresses in order to expand their client base. The main task of an email marketer is to establish contact with potential consumers and build trusting relationships with them.
Almost all Email Marketers work with other specialists such as [copywriters,](/copywriter/) [designers](/designer/), [SMM](/smm-manager/) and [SEO managers](/seo-manager/). ## Day-to-day responsibilities. Email marketer is responsible for:
* Email marketing strategy development;
* Digital audience analysis;
* Creating and customizing email content;
* Dealing with follower base;
* Choosing the letter style and adjusting it for a specific situation, event, or news;
Making up the text of the letter, defining the visual content.
## Email Marketing specialist. Skills needed to succeed:
* Fluency in English;
* Desire to grow and develop;
* Good written and verbal communication skills;
* Ability to work with a large volume of information;
* Advanced PC user;
* Experience in text writing;
* Knowledge of Photo editors (beneficial).
## Feel free to apply for the vacancy
Don’t worry if you do not have enough experience. At RemotEmployees you will have the opportunity to master new skills and improve them in practice.

## Who is a traffic manager?
The traffic manager is a relatively new profession that is taking the world by storm. This is because there has been a rise in the use of the Internet to promote products and because there is a chance to become an expert quickly and start working after taking courses or learning about the Internet.

A traffic manager is an advertisement management specialist, a person who is responsible for ad placement and everything related to the advertisement.
We can see only the “tip of the iceberg,” but traffic specialists and their teams have a great deal of work to do in order to make this “tip of the iceberg” appealing to customers and encourage them to buy a product that is being advertised, or at least leave their contact information.
This is a full-time remote job in our company. We are ready to employ Traffic managers even without work experience. We provide on-the-job training and round-the-clock support for our newcomers.## Responsibilities of the traffic manager include:
* Work with advertising accounts (Google Ads, Facebook, Instagram, etc.);
* Advertising campaigns creation;
* Advertising campaigns analysis;
* Work with other team members: designers, copywriters;
* Ability to hold A/B testing of campaigns;
* Аccount keeping;
* Dealing with budgets.
## Who fits the position of a Remote Traffic Manager?
The Traffic manager has a lot of tasks to execute, but still, they are all intertwined. If you are creative and a “numbers person,” – we are waiting for you to join our friendly team. We are ready to help you with training and pave the way from the very beginning to the creation of your first advertisement.
A traffic specialist is responsible for attracting new customers and analyzing the results of their own work. This is an essential element in order to find the most successful and profitable means of attracting an audience. This is a work-from-home position, and you need only a computer and a stable Internet connection. Start mastering the traffic manager profession today at RemotEmployees.
Record [videointerview](/videointerview) and tell us about your skills and knowledge and we'll contact you as soon as possible!

## Who is a PR Manager?
A PR manager (public relations manager) is a media and public relations specialist responsible for planning and directing the creation of materials in order to support or improve the public image of their employer or client.## Responsibilities of the PR Manager include:
 The responsibilities of the PR manager vacancy will include:
* Working with online publications around the world;
* Publishing or posting promotional materials and reviews about our company;
* Analysis of site owners according to the indicators we provided and work with spreadsheet applications;
* Organization of work on public relations and mass media.

You will master skills such as analyzing the quality of media resources, types of audiences, and proficiency in online analysis tools. If you already have such skills, it will be a big benefit.## Basic requirements for a PR Manager are:
* Understanding the principle of content creation – from ordinary texts to multimedia;
* Excellent command of written and spoken English;
* Be advanced enough to work with social media;
* PC proficiency (MS Office, Google Drive, Data Search).
To apply for this position, you will need to record a [videointerview](/videointerview) in English and complete a test task. We will be happy to consider your candidacy.
